content:
Certainly! Here’s a creative proverb incorporating the keywords "expectations" and "success":

"Lower your expectations, elevate your efforts, and let success be your surprise."

To display this proverb on your website in an aesthetically pleasing way, here's some HTML and CSS code:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Proverb Display</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f9;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
        }
        .proverb-container {
            background-color: #ffffff;
            padding: 20px 40px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            max-width: 600px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .proverb {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            color: #333333;
            margin: 0;
        }
        .highlight {
            color: #007BFF;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="proverb-container">
    <p class="proverb">Lower your <span class="highlight">expectations</span>, elevate your efforts, and let <span class="highlight">success</span> be your surprise.</p>
</div>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **HTML Structure**: The proverb is enclosed in a `div` with a class of `proverb-container` to style it properly.
- **Styling**: 
  - The overall layout uses Flexbox to center the content vertically and horizontally.
  - The `proverb-container` has a background, padding, rounded corners, and a subtle shadow to make it stand out.
  - The keywords "expectations" and "success" are highlighted in a different color and bold font for emphasis.
- **Responsive Design**: The text size and container width are set to be flexible and look good on different screen sizes.

Feel free to adjust the styles to better match your website's theme and design!
